In geometry, Heron's formula (sometimes called Hero's formula), 
named after Hero of Alexandria,[1] gives the area of a triangle 
when the length of all three sides are known. Unlike other triangle 
area formulae, there is no need to calculate angles or other distances 
in the triangle first.

